DIRECTIONS TO NYU           The Food and Climate Summit will take place at New York University on Saturday, December 12, 2009.              The morning plenary session will be held in the Jack H. Skirball Center for the Performing Arts, located at 566 LaGuardia Place at Washington Square South.     The rest of the days sessions will be held upstairs in the adjoining Kimmel Center for University Life at 60 Washington Square South.     The entrances to both locations are at the corner of Washington Square South and LaGuardia Place.              CAMPUS MAP         The NYU campus map is available at http://www.nyu.edu/about/campus.map.pdf . The Kimmel Center/Skirball Center building is #47 on the map.         BY SUBWAY          Tip: For point-to-point directions using public transportation, visit www.hopstop.com .     Tip: Weekend subway service is frequently altered. Check for service disruptions before you travel. [ http://tripplanner.mta.info/NewTP/serviceAdvisories/ServiceAdvisoryAll.aspx ]              A, C, E, D, F, V trains : Take to the West 4th Street Station. To exit the station, follow the signs to the West 3rd Street exit. Walk north one block on Sixth Avenue, turn right (east) onto West 4th Street. Continue walking on West 4th Street as it becomes Washington Square South. Continue until you reach the Kimmel Center at 60 Washington Square South. Turn right onto LaGuardia Place to find the Skirball Center entrance.          No. 6 train : Take the Lexington Avenue subway to the Astor Place Station. Go west on Astor Place to Broadway. Walk south on Broadway about three blocks to West 4th Street. Turn right onto West 4th Street and continue walking for four blocks as the street becomes Washington Square South. Turn left onto LaGuardia Place to access the Skirball Center entrance, or enter the Kimmel Center at 60 Washington Square South.          N or R trains : Take to the 8th Street Station. Walk south on Broadway about three blocks to West 4th Street. Turn right onto West 4th Street and continue walking for four blocks as the street becomes Washington Square South. Turn left onto LaGuardia Place to access the Skirball Center entrance, or enter the Kimmel Center at 60 Washington Square South.          No. 1 train : Take the Seventh Avenue subway to Christopher Street-Sheridan Square. Walk east on West 4th Street for about six blocks as it becomes Washington Square South. Continue until you reach the Kimmel Center at 60 Washington Square South. Turn right onto LaGuardia Place to find the Skirball Center entrance.            BY TRAIN          PATH Trains from New Jersey : Take the PATH train to 9th Street Station (Sixth Avenue and 9th Street). Walk south along Sixth Avenue to West Fourth Street. Turn left onto West 4th Street and continue walking as it becomes Washington Square South. Continue until you reach the Kimmel Center at 60 Washington Square South. Turn right onto LaGuardia Place to find the Skirball Center entrance.           Metro North into Grand Central Station : Take the Lexington Avenue subway (No. 6 train) downtown from Grand Central to Astor Place Station. Follow walking directions for No. 6 train above.           Long Island Rail Road (LIRR) and Amtrak into Pennsylvania Station : Take the Eighth Avenue subway (A, C and E trains) downtown from 34th Street to West 4th Street Station. Follow walking directions for A, C, and E trains above.           BY BUS           All Greyhound and New Jersey Transit buses go to the Port Authority Terminal. From the Port Authority/42nd Street Subway Station, take the Eighth Avenue subway (A, C and E trains) downtown. Follow walking directions for A, C, and E trains above.           PARKING           Thompson Street Garage     221 Thompson St., Between 3rd St. and Bleecker St., 212.677.8741          Washington Square Garage     2 Fifth Ave., Between 8th St. and Washington Square North, 212.533.8312          Champion Parking     60-68 East 8th Street, Between Waverly and 8th St., 212.308.5959          Eighth Street Parking Corp.     11 8th St. at Fifth Ave., 212.475.9562          Hillary Gardens Garage     300 Mercer St., Between 8th St. and Waverly Pl., (or enter via Broadway side), 212.473.8752          Washington Square Village Garage     1 Washington Square Village, Between 3rd St. and Bleecker St., 212.253.9061          Brevoort Parking Corp.     12-20 East 9th St., Between Fifth Ave. and University Pl., 212.873.8220          Guardian Thomas Corp.     63 East 9th St., Between Broadway and University Pl., 212.463.6000                 BY CAR           Tip: We recommend using an online service for driving instructions, such as Google Maps [ http://maps.google.com/ ] or Mapquest [ http://www.mapquest.com/ ].           For general driving instructions to Washington Square, see below.           From the Bronx and Upstate NY     Take the NY State Thruway, which becomes the Major Deegan Expressway in the Bronx, to the Triborough Bridge (toll). Cross to Manhattan taking the FDR Drive. Follow the FDR Drive south to Houston Street. Continue west on Houston Street past Broadway to LaGuardia Place. Turn right (north) and follow LaGuardia Place to Washington Square.           From Connecticut     Take the New England Thruway (I-95) into the Bronx. Then, take the Bruckner Expressway (I-278) to the Triborough Bridge (toll). Cross to Manhattan taking the FDR Drive south to Houston Street. Continue west on Houston Street past Broadway to LaGuardia Place. Turn right (north) and follow LaGuardia Place to Washington Square.           From the Northwest, West, and South including New Jersey     Take I-95 and/or the New Jersey Turnpike to the Lincoln Tunnel or the Holland Tunnel. If taking the Lincoln tunnel, take the right tube and stay in the right lane, turning right onto Dyer Ave. after exiting the tunnel. Go through three lights, making a left on to 34th St. and move to the right lane. After one block, turn left onto 9th Ave., continuing south until 14th St. Turn left onto 14th St., followed by a right onto 5th Ave., until it ends at Washington Square. If taking the Holland tunnel, there will be a circle after exiting. Take the Canal St. East exit. After a few lights, turn left onto West Broadway. Proceed north until you reach Washington Square.           From the George Washington Bridge     Take the Henry Hudson Parkway (turns into the West Side Highway/12th Avenue) south to 23rd Street. Turn left (east) on 23rd Street to Fifth Avenue. Turn right (south) on Fifth Avenue to Washington Square. Circle to the south side of the park to find the Kimmel Center.           From Brooklyn     Take the Manhattan Bridge. Off the bridge, take Canal Street west to Sixth Avenue. Take Sixth Avenue north to West Fourth Street and travel east to Washington Square.           From Queens     Take the 59th Street Bridge and turn left (south) on Fifth Avenue. Fifth Avenue ends at the Washington Square campus. Circle to the south side of the park to find the Kimmel Center.           From Staten Island     Take the Staten Island Express across the Verrazano-Narrows Bridge crossing into Brooklyn. Take the Belt Parkway west to the Brooklyn-Queens Expressway (BQE) east. Take the Manhattan Bridge exit, cross over the bridge, and take Canal Street west to Sixth Avenue. Turn right (north) on to Sixth Avenue to West 4th Street. Turn right (east) and travel to Washington Square.           From Long Island     Take the Long Island Expressway (also called the L.I.E. or I-495) west to the Queens-Midtown Tunnel. Drive west on 37th Street to Fifth Avenue. Turn left (south) on Fifth Avenue until it ends at the Washington Square campus.

DIRECTIONS TO NYU           The Food and Climate Summit will take place at New York University on Saturday, December 12, 2009.              The morning plenary session will be held in the Jack H. Skirball Center for the Performing Arts, located at 566 LaGuardia Place at Washington Square South.     The rest of the days sessions will be held upstairs in the adjoining Kimmel Center for University Life at 60 Washington Square South.     The entrances to both locations are at the corner of Washington Square South and LaGuardia Place.              CAMPUS MAP         The NYU campus map is available at http://www.nyu.edu/about/campus.map.pdf . The Kimmel Center/Skirball Center building is #47 on the map.         BY SUBWAY          Tip: For point-to-point directions using public transportation, visit www.hopstop.com .     Tip: Weekend subway service is frequently altered. Check for service disruptions before you travel. [ http://tripplanner.mta.info/NewTP/serviceAdvisories/ServiceAdvisoryAll.aspx ]              A, C, E, D, F, V trains : Take to the West 4th Street Station. To exit the station, follow the signs to the West 3rd Street exit. Walk north one block on Sixth Avenue, turn right (east) onto West 4th Street. Continue walking on West 4th Street as it becomes Washington Square South. Continue until you reach the Kimmel Center at 60 Washington Square South. Turn right onto LaGuardia Place to find the Skirball Center entrance.          No. 6 train : Take the Lexington Avenue subway to the Astor Place Station. Go west on Astor Place to Broadway. Walk south on Broadway about three blocks to West 4th Street. Turn right onto West 4th Street and continue walking for four blocks as the street becomes Washington Square South. Turn left onto LaGuardia Place to access the Skirball Center entrance, or enter the Kimmel Center at 60 Washington Square South.          N or R trains : Take to the 8th Street Station. Walk south on Broadway about three blocks to West 4th Street. Turn right onto West 4th Street and continue walking for four blocks as the street becomes Washington Square South. Turn left onto LaGuardia Place to access the Skirball Center entrance, or enter the Kimmel Center at 60 Washington Square South.          No. 1 train : Take the Seventh Avenue subway to Christopher Street-Sheridan Square. Walk east on West 4th Street for about six blocks as it becomes Washington Square South. Continue until you reach the Kimmel Center at 60 Washington Square South. Turn right onto LaGuardia Place to find the Skirball Center entrance.            BY TRAIN          PATH Trains from New Jersey : Take the PATH train to 9th Street Station (Sixth Avenue and 9th Street). Walk south along Sixth Avenue to West Fourth Street. Turn left onto West 4th Street and continue walking as it becomes Washington Square South. Continue until you reach the Kimmel Center at 60 Washington Square South. Turn right onto LaGuardia Place to find the Skirball Center entrance.           Metro North into Grand Central Station : Take the Lexington Avenue subway (No. 6 train) downtown from Grand Central to Astor Place Station. Follow walking directions for No. 6 train above.           Long Island Rail Road (LIRR) and Amtrak into Pennsylvania Station : Take the Eighth Avenue subway (A, C and E trains) downtown from 34th Street to West 4th Street Station. Follow walking directions for A, C, and E trains above.           BY BUS           All Greyhound and New Jersey Transit buses go to the Port Authority Terminal. From the Port Authority/42nd Street Subway Station, take the Eighth Avenue subway (A, C and E trains) downtown. Follow walking directions for A, C, and E trains above.           PARKING           Thompson Street Garage     221 Thompson St., Between 3rd St. and Bleecker St., 212.677.8741          Washington Square Garage     2 Fifth Ave., Between 8th St. and Washington Square North, 212.533.8312          Champion Parking     60-68 East 8th Street, Between Waverly and 8th St., 212.308.5959          Eighth Street Parking Corp.     11 8th St. at Fifth Ave., 212.475.9562          Hillary Gardens Garage     300 Mercer St., Between 8th St. and Waverly Pl., (or enter via Broadway side), 212.473.8752          Washington Square Village Garage     1 Washington Square Village, Between 3rd St. and Bleecker St., 212.253.9061          Brevoort Parking Corp.     12-20 East 9th St., Between Fifth Ave. and University Pl., 212.873.8220          Guardian Thomas Corp.     63 East 9th St., Between Broadway and University Pl., 212.463.6000                 BY CAR           Tip: We recommend using an online service for driving instructions, such as Google Maps [ http://maps.google.com/ ] or Mapquest [ http://www.mapquest.com/ ].           For general driving instructions to Washington Square, see below.           From the Bronx and Upstate NY     Take the NY State Thruway, which becomes the Major Deegan Expressway in the Bronx, to the Triborough Bridge (toll). Cross to Manhattan taking the FDR Drive. Follow the FDR Drive south to Houston Street. Continue west on Houston Street past Broadway to LaGuardia Place. Turn right (north) and follow LaGuardia Place to Washington Square.           From Connecticut     Take the New England Thruway (I-95) into the Bronx. Then, take the Bruckner Expressway (I-278) to the Triborough Bridge (toll). Cross to Manhattan taking the FDR Drive south to Houston Street. Continue west on Houston Street past Broadway to LaGuardia Place. Turn right (north) and follow LaGuardia Place to Washington Square.           From the Northwest, West, and South including New Jersey     Take I-95 and/or the New Jersey Turnpike to the Lincoln Tunnel or the Holland Tunnel. If taking the Lincoln tunnel, take the right tube and stay in the right lane, turning right onto Dyer Ave. after exiting the tunnel. Go through three lights, making a left on to 34th St. and move to the right lane. After one block, turn left onto 9th Ave., continuing south until 14th St. Turn left onto 14th St., followed by a right onto 5th Ave., until it ends at Washington Square. If taking the Holland tunnel, there will be a circle after exiting. Take the Canal St. East exit. After a few lights, turn left onto West Broadway. Proceed north until you reach Washington Square.           From the George Washington Bridge     Take the Henry Hudson Parkway (turns into the West Side Highway/12th Avenue) south to 23rd Street. Turn left (east) on 23rd Street to Fifth Avenue. Turn right (south) on Fifth Avenue to Washington Square. Circle to the south side of the park to find the Kimmel Center.           From Brooklyn     Take the Manhattan Bridge. Off the bridge, take Canal Street west to Sixth Avenue. Take Sixth Avenue north to West Fourth Street and travel east to Washington Square.           From Queens     Take the 59th Street Bridge and turn left (south) on Fifth Avenue. Fifth Avenue ends at the Washington Square campus. Circle to the south side of the park to find the Kimmel Center.           From Staten Island     Take the Staten Island Express across the Verrazano-Narrows Bridge crossing into Brooklyn. Take the Belt Parkway west to the Brooklyn-Queens Expressway (BQE) east. Take the Manhattan Bridge exit, cross over the bridge, and take Canal Street west to Sixth Avenue. Turn right (north) on to Sixth Avenue to West 4th Street. Turn right (east) and travel to Washington Square.           From Long Island     Take the Long Island Expressway (also called the L.I.E. or I-495) west to the Queens-Midtown Tunnel. Drive west on 37th Street to Fifth Avenue. Turn left (south) on Fifth Avenue until it ends at the Washington Square campus.
